title: Aleksandr Golovnya (footballer, born 1998)
text:
Aleksandr Yegorovich Golovnya (; born 27 October 1998) is a Russian <a href="association%20football">football</a> player. He plays for Armenian club <a href="FC%20Noah">FC Noah</a> on loan from <a href="FC%20Rodina%20Moscow">FC Rodina Moscow</a>.
Club career.
He made his debut in the <a href="Russian%20Professional%20Football%20League">Russian Professional Football League</a> for <a href="FC%20Solyaris%20Moscow">FC Solyaris Moscow</a> on 2 October 2016 in a game against <a href="FC%20Torpedo%20Vladimir">FC Torpedo Vladimir</a>.
He made his <a href="Russian%20Football%20National%20League">Russian Football National League</a> debut for <a href="FC%20Tyumen">FC Tyumen</a> on 16 September 2017 in a game against <a href="FC%20Dynamo%20Saint%20Petersburg">FC Dynamo Saint Petersburg</a>.
On 7 August 2020, he joined <a href="Russian%20Premier%20League">Russian Premier League</a> club <a href="FC%20Tambov">FC Tambov</a> on a season-long loan. He made his Russian Premier League debut for Tambov on 22 August 2020 in a game against <a href="FC%20Zenit%20Saint%20Petersburg">FC Zenit Saint Petersburg</a>. His loan was terminated by Tambov on 9 October 2020.
